.TH hsh 1 "5 August 2022" "Simple Shell"
.SH NAME
hs - command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
This project consist of the development of a command interpreter for Linux. The program tries to replicate the basic functionalities of sh shell. It was developed in C language.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Overview
The hsh utility shall execute commands read from a command line string, the standar input, or a specified file. It has a interactive and non-interactive mode, commands can be typed directly to the running shell or can be put into a file to be executed.
.sp 1
There are three types of command that can be interpreted by the shell: system calls, commands, or commands with to be found in a given specified route.
If the command name doesn't match a built-in, and it's route is not specified, it will be searched through all PATH directories.
.SH AUTHOR
Ismael Soler & Ignacio Martino

